---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="Leter abuse reporting policy." />
    <title>Abuse Reporting | leter.net</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="min-h-screen bg-surface">
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text">‚Üê Back to home</a>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text">Abuse Reporting</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: February 15, 2026</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-muted">
          <p>
            leter.net operates under a strict anti-abuse policy. Reports are reviewed by
            <a
              class="text-text underline decoration-accent/60 underline-offset-2"
              href="https://lewsion.com"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              Lewsion Ltd.
            </a>
            to protect users, recipients, and infrastructure trust.
          </p>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">1. What should be reported</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Report any suspected abuse tied to `@leter.net` identities, including spam, phishing,
              fraud, impersonation, malware distribution, credential theft, and other harmful
              activity.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Banks, payment processors, compliance teams, legal teams, and affected recipients may
              submit reports. Requests to investigate and disable abusive identities are accepted.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">2. Evidence to include</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">Include as much verifiable detail as possible:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>full sender address and impacted recipient address(es);</li>
              <li>timestamps (preferably UTC);</li>
              <li>full email headers and raw message source (if available);</li>
              <li>message body, links, or attachment indicators;</li>
              <li>case IDs from banks, providers, or legal teams (if applicable).</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">3. Enforcement flow</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Lewsion may issue warnings for lower-risk misuse. For severe or repeated abuse,
              identities may be suspended, seized, or permanently disabled.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Where appropriate and operationally feasible, reporters and affected parties may
              receive acknowledgment that review was completed.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">4. Reporting contacts</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Abuse: <span class="text-text">abuse@lewsion.com</span>
              <br />
              Legal escalation: <span class="text-text">legal@lewsion.com</span>
              <br />
              Copyright notices: use
              <a class="text-text underline decoration-accent/60 underline-offset-2" href="/dmca">
                DMCA process
              </a>
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
